        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3522331969" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9702785579418232432">I remember reading this story in 8th or 9th grade; ever since, the premise and hilarity of O. Henry&apos;s handiwork would randomly pop into my head. <br/><br/>And then today, one of my awesome friends posted a review for it COMPLETE WITH A LINK TO THE FULL STORY (it&apos;s only 16 pages long). And I smashed the link and read it right then and there. Still just as funny. Maybe funnier. <br/><br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;source=web&amp;rct=j&amp;url=https://dwcaonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Henry_Red_Chief.pdf&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjKuvb2rcLrAhUMCc0KHZ47C6EQFjAAegQICBAB&amp;usg=AOvVaw0dH0TTIT-MHjioeaEJnLaU'>https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;s...</a><br/><br/>Sidebar: this was written in 1910, so there are some racial references that may make some peopl</span>
  <span id="freeText9702785579418232432" style="display:none">I remember reading this story in 8th or 9th grade; ever since, the premise and hilarity of O. Henry's handiwork would randomly pop into my head. <br /><br />And then today, one of my awesome friends posted a review for it COMPLETE WITH A LINK TO THE FULL STORY (it's only 16 pages long). And I smashed the link and read it right then and there. Still just as funny. Maybe funnier. <br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;source=web&amp;rct=j&amp;url=https://dwcaonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Henry_Red_Chief.pdf&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjKuvb2rcLrAhUMCc0KHZ47C6EQFjAAegQICBAB&amp;usg=AOvVaw0dH0TTIT-MHjioeaEJnLaU">https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;s...</a><br /><br />Sidebar: this was written in 1910, so there are some racial references that may make some people squirm. They aren't being used maliciously in any way; it was part of the vernacular back then. If this will bother you, don't pick this one up. <br /><br />I'd rate this book a PG for the racial references and violence.</span>
