<div id="review_940767695" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/940767695" />
    <a title="Realini" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7873218-realini"><img alt="Realini" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1420269105p2/7873218.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/940767695?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Realini" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Realini" href="/user/show/7873218-realini">Realini</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7873218-realini?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer940767695" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14052846040007073738">The Ransom of Red Chief by O. Henry<br/><br/>You Must Read This: it is short, but packed full with fabulous, uproarious moments!!<br/>This is hilarious and one of the funniest short stories I have read in quite a while.<br/>“It looked like a good thing: but wait till I tell you. “<br/>You are warned from the start and the plot is revealed in the next couple of sentences: Bill Driscoll and the narrator plan to kidnap a boy, who turns out to be Winnetou, Old Shatterhand and Dracula all mixed into one. <br/>This brought to my m</span>
  <span id="freeText14052846040007073738" style="display:none">The Ransom of Red Chief by O. Henry<br /><br />You Must Read This: it is short, but packed full with fabulous, uproarious moments!!<br />This is hilarious and one of the funniest short stories I have read in quite a while.<br />“It looked like a good thing: but wait till I tell you. “<br />You are warned from the start and the plot is revealed in the next couple of sentences: Bill Driscoll and the narrator plan to kidnap a boy, who turns out to be Winnetou, Old Shatterhand and Dracula all mixed into one. <br />This brought to my mind the famous:<br />“You Can’t Handle the Truth” outburst of Jack Nicholson in A Few Good Men.<br />The boy, who was supposed to be submissive and bring a lot of cash, turns out to be too much to handle in a sequence of funny and unexpected turns of events.<br />We expect people who plot such a serious and heinous crime as taking away a little boy to be vicious, cruel and in control.<br />Well, not in this story they ain’t.<br />The son of Ebenezer Dorset gives from first glance a warning sign, throwing a rock at the head of our miscreants.<br />They should have known better: the boy plays The Red Chief from the title and is “As Good As It Gets „to use another title from the Jack Nicholson paraphernalia.<br />Red Chief is so serious about his role that Bill Driscol is finished off, kaput, terminated. His only remaining goal in life is to end a life of misery, under the complete control of his Red Chief, who resorts to riding Bill….literally.<br />I won’t give you the glorious and shocking finale, to avoid spoiling the surprise, the laughter which will seize you.<br />Please read it and then thank me!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14052846040007073738" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


