<div id="review_1752773482" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1752773482" />
    <a title="Author-ization" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48938832-author-ization"><img alt="Author-ization" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1483411790p2/48938832.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1752773482?book_show_action=true">Sep 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Author-ization" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Author-ization" href="/user/show/48938832-author-ization">Author-ization</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1752773482" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6660285923759739973">This was nice and well-written. Plus it was funny! I would say the humor compelled me to add another star to the rating.<br/>The certain descriptions of the little boy the two men kidnapped and his numerous role-playing games he wanted to play eventually weakened the men, which was funny!<br/>Our mains Sam and Bill create an enjoyable dynamic commonly found in stories much like this. Sam was the small, mellow &quot;brain&quot; of the duo and Bill is the big fat brute, albeit easily scared by a ten year-old kid. It </span>
  <span id="freeText6660285923759739973" style="display:none">This was nice and well-written. Plus it was funny! I would say the humor compelled me to add another star to the rating.<br />The certain descriptions of the little boy the two men kidnapped and his numerous role-playing games he wanted to play eventually weakened the men, which was funny!<br />Our mains Sam and Bill create an enjoyable dynamic commonly found in stories much like this. Sam was the small, mellow "brain" of the duo and Bill is the big fat brute, albeit easily scared by a ten year-old kid. It wasn't the central theme of this story but definitely noticeable through dialogue and the way different ways they reacted to the same situations. <br />Nothing in this is though-provoking, but it <i>is</i> an enjoyable read if you're looking to easily add something to your <i>read</i> pile.<br />You'll get the meaning of the title once you get at least a quarter into the story, by the way.<br />The ending was the best part, in my opinion! You have to read it to see for yourself. ;)<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6660285923759739973" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


